 yet at the same time some women have been inhibited since many conservative circles use these new technologies to maintain their power. Overall, however, Al-Rawi argues that social media and new mobile technologies are assisting in creating changes that are predominately positive. Often assisted by these new technologies, the real change makers are women who have clear agencies and high hopes and aspirations to create a better future for themselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminismzArab countries. 0aMass media and womenzArab countries. 0aSocial movementszArab countries. 0aWomenxPolitical activityzArab countries. 4aArea Studies : Middle East Studies. 4aCommunication : Communication. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aScience, Mathematics, and Technology : Internet. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2020z978311149149340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847867840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438478678423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438478678/original  a978-3-11-149149-3  SUNY Press eBook Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles